{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894999179,"sessionID":"ses_28469878bffeybK3r1jPZRgBux","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9730380012Nx2BKLZX6JLEu","messageID":"msg_d7b96822d001lsTyK54Ec2DjWI","sessionID":"ses_28469878bffeybK3r1jPZRgBux","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f460f961a8934f7185328c3872bd24c1","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Python SDK/CLI Testing — Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification defines test scenarios for validating the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) and CLI functionality, building upon the base design and specification documents.\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Unit test coverage for SDK components\n\n#### Scenario: Test `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` success\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` with valid `base_url` and `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=1800)` is called and the mock server returns `{\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that the HTTP request used `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, the request body contained `{\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\",\"ttl\":1800,\"metadata\":null}`, and the method returns `\"session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session` handles 404\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` configured with valid credentials\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\")` is called and the mock server returns 404\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that the method returns `True` (404 treated as success)\n\n#### Scenario: Test `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session` handles failure\n- **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` configured with valid credentials\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(\"session-123\")` is called and the mock server returns 500\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that the method logs the error and returns `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command` success\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id=\"session-123\"` and mocked HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called and the mock returns `{\"stdout\":\"hello\\n\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"exitCode\":0}`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request posted to `api/execute` with body `{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"hello\"],\"timeout\":\"122.0s\"}` and the method returns the `stdout` value\n\n#### Scenario: Test `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command` non-zero exit\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id=\"session-123\"` and mocked HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"exit 1\")` is called and the mock returns `{\"stdout\":\"\",\"stderr\":\"error\",\"exitCode\":1}`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `CommandExecutionError` is raised with `exit_code=1`, `stderr=\"error\"`, and `command=[\"exit\",\"1\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `CodeInterpreterClient.run_code` with Python\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` with mocked data plane and control plane\n- **WHEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `write_file` was called with a `.py` file containing the code and `execute_command` was called with `python3 <filename>`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id` success\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `router_url=\"http://router\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `agent_name=\"test-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called and the GET request returns header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-456`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the GET request went to the correct URL and the method returns `\"session-456\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id` missing header\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` configured for a valid agent\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called and the response lacks the session header\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `ValueError` is raised with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Test `read_token_from_file` success\n- **GIVEN** a temporary file containing `\"test-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the function returns `\"test-token\"` (whitespace stripped)\n\n#### Scenario: Test `read_token_from_file` missing file\n- **GIVEN** a non-existent file path\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the function returns `\"\"` (empty string)\n\n### Requirement: Integration test for CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n\n#### Scenario: Full lifecycle with context manager\n- **GIVEN** a test environment with mocked Workload Manager and Router endpoints\n- **WHEN** the following code executes:\n  ```python\n  with CodeInterpreterClient(\n      name=\"test-int\",\n      namespace=\"test-ns\",\n      workload_manager_url=\"http://wm-mock\",\n      router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n  ) as client:\n      result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'integration test'\")\n  ```\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - `POST` to Workload Manager created a session\n  - Data plane client was initialized with the session ID\n  - `execute_command` returned the expected output\n  - `DELETE` to Workload Manager cleaned up the session on exit\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL not provided raises error\n- **GIVEN** no `ROUTER_URL` environment variable and no `router_url` argument\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `ValueError` is raised with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n\n### Requirement: Integration test for AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime invoke flow\n- **GIVEN** a test environment with mocked Router endpoint that provides session ID on GET\n- **WHEN** the following code executes:\n  ```python\n  with AgentRuntimeClient(\n      agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n      namespace=\"test-ns\",\n      router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n  ) as client:\n      response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n  ```\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - `GET` request bootstrapped the session ID\n  - `POST` request invoked the agent with the payload\n  - Context manager closed the HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime invoke without session ID\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` with `session_id=None`\n- **WHEN** `invoke({\"message\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `ValueError` is raised with message `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"`\n\n### Requirement: File operations testing\n\n#### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with mocked HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `write_file(\"hello world\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request body contains base64-encoded `\"aGVsbG8gd29ybGQ=\"`, `path=\"/tmp/test.txt\"`, and `mode=\"0644\"`\n\n#### Scenario: List files returns parsed JSON\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with mocked HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `list_files(\"/tmp\")` is called and the mock returns `[{\"name\":\"test.txt\",\"size\":11}]`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request used `GET api/files?path=/tmp` and the method returns the parsed JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Download file streams response\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with mocked HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `download_file(\"/tmp/test.txt\", \"/local/test.txt\")` is called with `stream=True`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - Request used `GET api/files/tmp/test.txt`\n  - Response content was written to the local file path\n  - Session header was included\n\n### Requirement: Timeout behavior testing\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command timeout override\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `timeout=120`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request body contains `timeout=\"32.0s\"` (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command default timeout\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `timeout=120`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo test\", timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request body contains `timeout=\"122.0s\"` (120 + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` with `timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0`\n- **WHEN** `invoke({\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request timeout is `(5.0, 120)`\n\n### Requirement: Session header management testing\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane requests include session header\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id=\"test-session\"`\n- **WHEN** any data plane method (`execute_command`, `write_file`, etc.) is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the request includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id=\"test-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/file.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the multipart request includes `data={\"path\":\"/remote/file.txt\",\"mode\":\"0644\"}` with session header\n\n### Requirement: HTTP client session pooling\n\n#### Scenario: create_session configures HTTPAdapter\n- **GIVEN** a call to `create_session(pool_connections=5, pool_maxsize=10)`\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify that `HTTPAdapter` is mounted for both `http://` and `https://` with the specified pool settings\n\n### Requirement: Environment variable resolution\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://wm-env\"`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized without `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the client uses `http://wm-env` as `base_url`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL=\"http://router-env\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is initialized without `router_url`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the client uses `http://router-env` as `router_url`\n\n### Requirement: Exception hierarchy usage\n\n#### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n- **GIVEN** a mocked response with `exitCode=1, stderr=\"command failed\"`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the exception has attributes `exit_code=1`, `stderr=\"command failed\"`, and `command` matching the input\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError is importable\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube.exceptions` module\n- **WHEN** the test imports `SessionError`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify `SessionError` is a subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError is importable\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube.exceptions` module\n- **WHEN** the test imports `DataPlaneError`\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify `DataPlaneError` is a subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n\n### Requirement: Public API exports\n\n#### Scenario: Root package exports\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify both classes are imported successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Clients submodule exports\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube.clients` submodule\n- **WHEN** all client classes are imported\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` are available\n\n### Requirement: Logger configuration\n\n#### Scenario: get_logger returns configured logger\n- **GIVEN** a call to `get_logger(\"test-logger\", level=logging.DEBUG)`\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the logger has name `\"test-logger\"` and level `logging.DEBUG`\n\n### Requirement: Context manager behavior\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` used as a context manager with an active session\n- **WHEN** the context exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - Data plane client is closed\n  - Control plane session is deleted if `session_id` was set\n  - Control plane HTTP session is closed\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient context manager passes through exception\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** an exception is raised within the context block\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - `__exit__` is called with exception info\n  - The exception is re-raised after cleanup\n  - Session cleanup still occurs\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the context exits\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the underlying `requests.Session` is closed\n\n### Requirement: Error recovery scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` with mocked components where `create_session` succeeds but `_init_data_plane` raises\n- **WHEN** the client is initialized\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - A warning is logged\n  - `delete_session(session_id)` is called to clean up\n  - `session_id` is set to `None`\n  - The exception is re-raised\n\n### Requirement: Close methods\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient.stop deletes session\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` with `session_id=\"active-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify:\n  - Data plane client is closed\n  - Control plane `delete_session(\"active-session\")` is called\n  - Control plane HTTP session is closed\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient.close closes session\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` with an active HTTP session\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the test SHALL verify the `requests.Session` is closed","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775894999170,"end":1775894999175}}}}
