{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895095279,"sessionID":"ses_28469878bffeybK3r1jPZRgBux","part":{"id":"prt_d7b98a675001GCVdFwaIwMQr0L","messageID":"msg_d7b973869001xeTQrD70glvr4J","sessionID":"ses_28469878bffeybK3r1jPZRgBux","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-4287174b0d5b4ae883834f570ae0d89e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# delta-spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `sdk-python/tests`\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\nTask: Add comprehensive unit tests for AgentCube Python SDK components\n\n## Base Specs\n\n- `python-sdk/design.md` — Package layout, client APIs, configuration, HTTP contracts\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` — SDK requirements with acceptance scenarios\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Unit tests for ControlPlaneClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: Create session success\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with base_url=\"http://wm-mock\" and auth_token=\"test-token\"\nWHEN create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\", metadata=None, ttl=1800) is called\nAND the mock server returns {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\nTHEN the HTTP request should be POST to \"/v1/code-interpreter\"\nAND the request body should contain {\"name\":\"test\",\"namespace\":\"default\",\"ttl\":1800,\"metadata\":null}\nAND the method should return \"session-123\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-002: Create session missing sessionId in response\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\nWHEN create_session is called and the mock returns {\"data\": {}}\nTHEN ValueError should be raised with message containing \"sessionId\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-003: Delete session with 404 response\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\nWHEN delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\") is called and the server returns 404\nTHEN the method should return True\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-004: Delete session with error response\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with valid configuration\nWHEN delete_session(\"session-123\") is called and the server returns 500\nTHEN the error should be logged\nAND the method should return False\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-005: Resolve workload manager URL from argument\n```gherkin\nGIVEN workload_manager_url=\"http://custom-wm\" argument\nAND WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable set to \"http://env-wm\"\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://custom-wm\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-006: Resolve workload manager URL from environment\n```gherkin\nGIVEN no workload_manager_url argument\nAND WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://env-wm\" environment variable set\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://env-wm\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-007: Resolve auth token from file\n```gherkin\nGIVEN no auth_token argument\nAND SA token file contains \"service-account-token\\n\"\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN Authorization header should be set to \"Bearer service-account-token\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-008: Close closes HTTP session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with an active HTTP session\nWHEN close is called\nTHEN the HTTP session should be closed\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Unit tests for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-009: Execute command success\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nAND a mocked HTTP session\nWHEN execute_command(\"echo hello\") is called\nAND the mock returns {\"stdout\":\"hello\\n\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"exitCode\":0}\nTHEN the request should POST to \"api/execute\"\nAND the request body should be {\"command\":[\"echo\",\"hello\"],\"timeout\":\"122.0s\"}\nAND the method should return the stdout value\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-010: Execute command with list command\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nWHEN execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\"]) is called\nAND the mock returns successful response\nTHEN the request body command should be [\"ls\",\"-la\"]\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-011: Execute command non-zero exit raises error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nWHEN execute_command(\"exit 1\") is called\nAND the mock returns {\"stdout\":\"\",\"stderr\":\"error\",\"exitCode\":1}\nTHEN CommandExecutionError should be raised with exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=[\"exit\",\"1\"]\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-012: Execute command timeout override\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\nWHEN execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0) is called\nTHEN the request body should contain timeout=\"32.0s\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-013: Execute command default timeout\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\nWHEN execute_command(\"echo test\", timeout=None) is called\nTHEN the request body should contain timeout=\"122.0s\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-014: Run code Python writes file and executes\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with mocked methods\nWHEN run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\") is called\nTHEN write_file should be called with a .py file containing the code\nAND execute_command should be called with \"python3 <filename>\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-015: Write file with base64 encoding\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nWHEN write_file(\"hello world\", \"/tmp/test.txt\") is called\nTHEN the request body should contain base64-encoded content\nAND the path should be \"/tmp/test.txt\"\nAND mode should be \"0644\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-016: Upload file multipart\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nAND a local file \"/local/file.txt\"\nWHEN upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/file.txt\") is called\nTHEN the request should be multipart POST\nAND the data should contain path=\"/remote/file.txt\" and mode=\"0644\"\nAND session header should be set\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-017: Download file streams response\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nWHEN download_file(\"/tmp/test.txt\", \"/local/test.txt\") is called\nAND the mock returns streaming response\nTHEN the request should be GET \"api/files/tmp/test.txt\"\nAND the response content should be written to local file\nAND stream=True should be used\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-018: List files returns JSON\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\nWHEN list_files(\"/tmp\") is called\nAND the mock returns [{\"name\":\"test.txt\",\"size\":11}]\nTHEN the request should be GET \"api/files?path=/tmp\"\nAND the method should return the parsed JSON\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-019: Base URL construction from router URL\n```gherkin\nGIVEN router_url=\"http://router\", namespace=\"default\", cr_name=\"test-ci\"\nAND base_url is not provided\nWHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test-ci/invocations/\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-020: Base URL uses provided value\n```gherkin\nGIVEN base_url=\"http://custom-base\" is provided\nWHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://custom-base\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-021: Session header included in requests\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\nWHEN any _request method is called\nTHEN the request should include header \"x-agentcube-session-id: test-session\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-022: Bootstrap session ID success\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with router_url=\"http://router\"\nAND namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"test-agent\"\nWHEN bootstrap_session_id() is called\nAND the GET request returns header \"x-agentcube-session-id: session-456\"\nTHEN the GET request should go to the correct URL\nAND the method should return \"session-456\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-023: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient configured for a valid agent\nWHEN bootstrap_session_id() is called\nAND the response lacks the session header\nTHEN ValueError should be raised with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-024: Invoke without session ID raises error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with session_id=None or falsy\nWHEN invoke(\"session-id\", {\"message\": \"test\"}) is called with empty session_id\nTHEN ValueError should be raised with message \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-025: Invoke success\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\nWHEN invoke(\"active-session\", {\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=None) is called\nAND the mock returns successful response\nTHEN the request should POST to base_url\nAND the request should include session header and JSON payload\nAND timeout should be (connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-026: Invoke with timeout override\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with timeout=120\nWHEN invoke(\"session-id\", {\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60.0) is called\nTHEN the request timeout should be (connect_timeout, 60.0)\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-027: Base URL construction\n```gherkin\nGIVEN router_url=\"http://router\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"test-agent\"\nWHEN AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-028: SESSION_HEADER constant\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient class\nWHEN the SESSION_HEADER class constant is accessed\nTHEN it should be \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Unit tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-029: Initialize with provided session_id\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with session_id=\"existing-session\"\nAND router_url=\"http://router\"\nWHEN the client is initialized\nTHEN create_session should NOT be called\nAND _init_data_plane should be called with session_id=\"existing-session\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-030: Initialize without session_id creates new session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient without session_id\nAND workload_manager_url=\"http://wm\", router_url=\"http://router\"\nWHEN the client is initialized\nAND create_session returns \"new-session-id\"\nTHEN _init_data_plane should be called with session_id=\"new-session-id\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-031: Data plane init failure after session create\n```gherkin\nGIVEN session_id was not provided\nAND create_session succeeds returning \"session-123\"\nAND _init_data_plane raises an exception\nWHEN the client is initialized\nTHEN a warning should be logged\nAND delete_session(\"session-123\") should be called\nAND session_id should be set to None\nAND the exception should be re-raised\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-032: Router URL required\n```gherkin\nGIVEN neither router_url argument nor ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\nWHEN CodeInterpreterClient.__init__ is called\nTHEN ValueError should be raised with message containing \"Router URL must be provided\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-033: Context manager normal exit\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient used as a context manager\nAND session_id was set\nWHEN the context block exits without exception\nTHEN __exit__ should call stop()\nAND stop should close data plane client\nAND stop should call delete_session if session_id is set\nAND stop should close control plane HTTP session\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-034: Context manager exception exit\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient used as a context manager\nAND an exception occurs within the context block\nWHEN the context block exits\nTHEN __exit__ should call stop() for cleanup\nAND the exception should be re-raised\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-035: Execute command delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN execute_command(\"echo test\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's execute_command should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-036: Run code delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN run_code(\"python\", \"print('test')\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's run_code should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-037: Write file delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN write_file(\"content\", \"/path/file.txt\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's write_file should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-038: Upload file delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN upload_file(\"/local/file\", \"/remote/file\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's upload_file should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-039: Download file delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN download_file(\"/remote/file\", \"/local/file\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's download_file should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-040: List files delegates to data plane\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\nWHEN list_files(\"/path\") is called\nTHEN the data plane client's list_files should be called with the same arguments\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-041: Stop closes data plane and deletes session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\nAND initialized data plane and control plane clients\nWHEN stop() is called\nTHEN data plane client's close should be called\nAND control plane's delete_session(\"active-session\") should be called\nAND control plane's close should be called\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n\n#### SCENARIO-042: Initialize with provided session_id\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with agent_name=\"test-agent\"\nAND session_id=\"existing-session\"\nAND router_url=\"http://router\"\nWHEN the client is initialized\nTHEN bootstrap_session_id should NOT be called\nAND the session_id should be \"existing-session\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-043: Initialize without session_id bootstraps\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with agent_name=\"test-agent\"\nAND no session_id provided\nAND router_url=\"http://router\"\nWHEN the client is initialized\nAND bootstrap_session_id returns \"bootstrapped-session\"\nTHEN the session_id should be \"bootstrapped-session\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-044: Context manager normal exit\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient used as a context manager\nWHEN the context block exits without exception\nTHEN __exit__ should call close()\nAND close should close the underlying requests.Session\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-045: Context manager exception exit\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient used as a context manager\nAND an exception occurs within the context block\nWHEN the context block exits\nTHEN __exit__ should call close()\nAND the exception should be re-raised\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-046: Invoke with valid session_id\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=\"active-session\"\nWHEN invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"}, timeout=None) is called\nAND the data plane client returns a response\nTHEN the data plane client's invoke should be called with session_id and payload\nAND the parsed response JSON should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-047: Invoke with timeout override\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with default timeout=120\nWHEN invoke({\"test\": \"data\"}, timeout=60.0) is called\nTHEN the data plane client's invoke should be called with timeout=60.0\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-048: Close closes HTTP session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeClient with an active requests.Session\nWHEN close() is called\nTHEN the requests.Session should be closed\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Unit tests for utility functions\n\n#### SCENARIO-049: read_token_from_file success\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a temporary file containing \"test-token\\n\"\nWHEN read_token_from_file(file_path) is called\nTHEN the function should return \"test-token\"\nAND whitespace should be stripped\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-050: read_token_from_file missing file\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a non-existent file path\nWHEN read_token_from_file(file_path) is called\nTHEN FileNotFoundError should be caught\nAND the function should return \"\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-051: create_session configures HTTPAdapter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN pool_connections=5 and pool_maxsize=10\nWHEN create_session is called\nTHEN HTTPAdapter should be mounted for \"http://\"\nAND HTTPAdapter should be mounted for \"https://\"\nAND pool_connections should be 5\nAND pool_maxsize should be 10\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-052: get_logger returns configured logger\n```gherkin\nGIVEN name=\"test-logger\" and level=logging.DEBUG\nWHEN get_logger(name, level) is called\nTHEN the returned logger should have name \"test-logger\"\nAND the logger should have level logging.DEBUG\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-053: get_logger with string level\n```gherkin\nGIVEN name=\"test-logger\" and level=\"INFO\"\nWHEN get_logger(name, level) is called\nTHEN the returned logger should have level logging.INFO\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Unit tests for exception hierarchy\n\n#### SCENARIO-054: CommandExecutionError attributes\n```gherkin\nGIVEN exit_code=1, stderr=\"command failed\", command=[\"test\", \"cmd\"]\nWHEN CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command) is instantiated\nTHEN error.exit_code should be 1\nAND error.stderr should be \"command failed\"\nAND error.command should be [\"test\", \"cmd\"]\nAND error message should contain \"exit 1\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-055: AgentCubeError is base exception\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the AgentCubeError class\nWHEN an instance is created\nTHEN it should be a subclass of Exception\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-056: CommandExecutionError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the CommandExecutionError class\nWHEN isinstance is checked\nTHEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-057: SessionError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the SessionError class\nWHEN isinstance is checked\nTHEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-058: DataPlaneError is subclass of AgentCubeError\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the DataPlaneError class\nWHEN isinstance is checked\nTHEN it should be a subclass of AgentCubeError\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Unit tests for public API exports\n\n#### SCENARIO-059: Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube package\nWHEN \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\" is executed\nTHEN CodeInterpreterClient should be imported successfully\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-060: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube package\nWHEN \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\" is executed\nTHEN AgentRuntimeClient should be imported successfully\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-061: Root __all__ contains only public exports\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube package\nWHEN __all__ is inspected\nTHEN it should contain [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\nAND it should NOT contain client classes\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-062: Clients submodule exports ControlPlaneClient\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is imported\nTHEN it should be available\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-063: Clients submodule exports CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\nWHEN CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is imported\nTHEN it should be available\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-064: Clients submodule exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n```gherkin\nGIVEN the agentcube.clients submodule\nWHEN AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is imported\nTHEN it should be available\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Integration tests for end-to-end flows\n\n#### SCENARIO-065: CodeInterpreterClient full lifecycle\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a test environment with mocked Workload Manager and Router endpoints\nWHEN the following code executes:\n  with CodeInterpreterClient(\n      name=\"test-int\",\n      namespace=\"test-ns\",\n      workload_manager_url=\"http://wm-mock\",\n      router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n  ) as client:\n      result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'integration test'\")\nTHEN POST to Workload Manager should create a session\nAND Data plane client should be initialized with the session ID\nAND execute_command should return the expected output\nAND DELETE to Workload Manager should clean up the session on exit\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-066: AgentRuntimeClient invoke flow\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a test environment with mocked Router endpoint\nWHEN the following code executes:\n  with AgentRuntimeClient(\n      agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n      namespace=\"test-ns\",\n      router_url=\"http://router-mock\"\n  ) as client:\n      response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\nTHEN GET request should bootstrap the session ID\nAND POST request should invoke the agent with the payload\nAND Context manager should close the HTTP session\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Environment variable resolution tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-067: Workload Manager URL from environment\n```gherkin\nGIVEN WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://wm-env\" environment variable set\nAND no workload_manager_url argument\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN base_url should be \"http://wm-env\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-068: Router URL from environment\n```gherkin\nGIVEN ROUTER_URL=\"http://router-env\" environment variable set\nAND no router_url argument\nWHEN CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\nTHEN router_url should be \"http://router-env\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-069: Auth token from SA file\n```gherkin\nGIVEN no auth_token argument\nAND SA token file at /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token contains \"sa-token\"\nWHEN ControlPlaneClient is initialized\nTHEN auth_token should be \"sa-token\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Timeout behavior tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-070: Control plane timeout defaults\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient without timeout arguments\nWHEN a request is made\nTHEN timeout should be (5.0, 120)\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-071: Control plane timeout override\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0\nWHEN a request is made\nTHEN timeout should be (3.0, 60)\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-072: CodeInterpreterClient timeout defaults\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient without timeout arguments\nWHEN a data plane operation is performed\nTHEN timeout should be (5.0, 120)\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-073: CodeInterpreterClient timeout override\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterClient with timeout=90, connect_timeout=4.0\nWHEN a data plane operation is performed\nTHEN timeout should be (4.0, 90)\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: HTTP connection pooling tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-074: ControlPlaneClient uses pooled session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient\nWHEN the HTTP session is inspected\nTHEN pool_connections should be 10\nAND pool_maxsize should be 10\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-075: DataPlaneClient uses pooled session\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nWHEN the HTTP session is inspected\nTHEN pool_connections should be 10\nAND pool_maxsize should be 10\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-076: Custom pool configuration\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ControlPlaneClient with pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=30\nWHEN the HTTP session is inspected\nTHEN pool_connections should be 20\nAND pool_maxsize should be 30\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: Session header management tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-077: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient sets session header\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\nWHEN _request is called\nTHEN the request should include \"x-agentcube-session-id: test-session\" header\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-078: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient uses SESSION_HEADER constant\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\nWHEN a request is made\nTHEN the session header name should be from SESSION_HEADER constant\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Error handling tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-079: Request timeout handled\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client and a request that times out\nWHEN the request is made\nTHEN requests.Timeout should be handled appropriately\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-080: Connection error handled\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client and a connection failure\nWHEN the request is made\nTHEN requests.ConnectionError should be handled appropriately\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-081: HTTP error handled\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client and a 500 response\nWHEN the request is made\nTHEN the error should be logged or raised appropriately\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: Logger tests\n\n#### SCENARIO-082: Client creates logger\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client with verbose=True\nWHEN the client is initialized\nTHEN a logger should be created\nAND the logger level should be appropriate for verbose mode\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-083: Client uses logger for operations\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client with verbose=True\nWHEN an operation is performed\nTHEN the operation should be logged\n```\n\n---\n\n## Test Structure\n\nTests should be organized as:\n- `tests/test_control_plane.py` — ControlPlaneClient tests\n- `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests\n- `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests\n- `tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` — CodeInterpreterClient tests\n- `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` — AgentRuntimeClient tests\n- `tests/test_utils.py` — Utility function tests\n- `tests/test_exceptions.py` — Exception class tests\n- `tests/test_integration.py` — Integration tests\n\n## Test Framework\n\n- Use `pytest` as the test framework\n- Use `responses` or `httpx_mock` for HTTP request mocking\n- Use `pytest-mock` for mocking objects\n- Use `pytest-cov` for coverage reporting\n\n## Coverage Goals\n\n- Unit test coverage: >80% for all SDK modules\n- Integration test coverage: Key end-to-end flows\n- Edge cases and error paths should be covered","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775895094949,"end":1775895095276}}}}
